---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/Layout.astro'
import Header from '../components/astro/Header.astro'
import Footer from '../components/astro/Footer.astro'
import Accordion from '../components/astro/Accordion.astro'
---

<BaseLayout title='Prostate Hub - Stage 3'>
    <Header />

    <main class='my-8 container mx-auto px-4'>
        <section class='text-center p-8 mb-8'>
            <h1 class='text-3xl font-bold mb-4'>
                Stage 3: Locally Advanced Prostate Cancer
            </h1>
            <p class='text-lg max-w-3xl mx-auto'>
                Information about Stage 3 prostate cancer, treatment options,
                and support for patients dealing with locally advanced disease.
            </p>
        </section>

        <div class='flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-8'>
            <div
                class='md:w-1/3 border border-gray-200 bg-fuchsia rounded-lg p-4'
            >
                <h2 class='text-xl font-bold mb-4'>Statistics</h2>
                <div class='space-y-4'>
                    <p>
                        Stage 3 prostate cancer has a 5-year survival rate of
                        approximately 80-90%.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        About 26% of men diagnosed with prostate cancer fall
                        into the high-risk group, which includes Stage 3.
                    </p>
                    <div
                        class='h-32 border border-gray-200 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center'
                    >
                        [Chart Placeholder: Treatment Success Rates for Stage 3]
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class='md:w-2/3'>
                <Accordion
                    title='What is Stage 3 Prostate Cancer?'
                    initiallyOpen={true}
                >
                    <div class='space-y-4'>
                        <p>
                            Stage 3 prostate cancer means the cancer has spread
                            beyond the prostate but has not yet reached distant
                            parts of the body. At this stage:
                        </p>
                        <ul class='list-disc pl-6 space-y-2'>
                            <li>
                                The cancer has extended beyond the outer layer
                                of the prostate
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                It may have spread to the seminal vesicles
                                (glands that help produce semen)
                            </li>
                            <li>PSA levels are typically above 20 ng/mL</li>
                            <li>The Gleason score is usually 7-10</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p>
                            Stage 3 is considered "locally advanced" and
                            requires more aggressive treatment than earlier
                            stages.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </Accordion>

                <Accordion title='Treatment Options'>
                    <div class='space-y-4'>
                        <h3 class='font-semibold text-lg'>Combined Approach</h3>
                        <p>
                            Stage 3 typically requires a multi-modal approach to
                            treatment. Options include:
                        </p>

                        <h3 class='font-semibold text-lg mt-6'>
                            External Beam Radiation with Hormone Therapy
                        </h3>
                        <p>
                            Often the primary treatment for Stage 3. This
                            usually involves:
                        </p>
                        <ul class='list-disc pl-6 space-y-2'>
                            <li>2-3 years of hormone therapy</li>
                            <li>6-8 weeks of radiation therapy</li>
                        </ul>

                        <h3 class='font-semibold text-lg mt-6'>
                            Radical Prostatectomy with Additional Treatments
                        </h3>
                        <p>Surgery may be performed, often followed by:</p>
                        <ul class='list-disc pl-6 space-y-2'>
                            <li>
                                Radiation therapy if cancer is found at the
                                surgical margins
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                Hormone therapy to reduce risk of recurrence
                            </li>
                        </ul>

                        <h3 class='font-semibold text-lg mt-6'>
                            Advanced Hormone Therapy
                        </h3>
                        <p>May include newer generation medications such as:</p>
                        <ul class='list-disc pl-6 space-y-2'>
                            <li>Abiraterone</li>
                            <li>Enzalutamide</li>
                            <li>Other androgen pathway inhibitors</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </Accordion>

                <Accordion title='Managing Side Effects'>
                    <div class='space-y-4'>
                        <p>
                            Treatment side effects at Stage 3 can be significant
                            and may include:
                        </p>
                        <ul class='list-disc pl-6 space-y-2'>
                            <li>Hot flashes from hormone therapy</li>
                            <li>Loss of bone density</li>
                            <li>Fatigue</li>
                            <li>Sexual dysfunction</li>
                            <li>Changes in body composition</li>
                            <li>Mood changes</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p>
                            Discuss side effect management strategies with your
                            healthcare team, which may include medications,
                            exercise, diet modifications, and supportive care.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </Accordion>

                <Accordion title='Support Options'>
                    <div class='space-y-4'>
                        <p>
                            Support is crucial for patients with Stage 3
                            prostate cancer:
                        </p>
                        <ul class='list-disc pl-6 space-y-2'>
                            <li>
                                <a
                                    href='#'
                                    class='text-blue-600 hover:underline'
                                    >Advanced Cancer Support Groups</a
                                >
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <a
                                    href='#'
                                    class='text-blue-600 hover:underline'
                                    >Mental Health Resources</a
                                >
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <a
                                    href='#'
                                    class='text-blue-600 hover:underline'
                                    >Family Support Services</a
                                >
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                        <p>
                            Regular communication with your healthcare team is
                            essential as treatment plans may need adjustment
                            based on your response and side effects.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </Accordion>

                <Accordion title='Clinical Trials'>
                    <div class='space-y-4'>
                        <p>
                            Clinical trials may offer access to newer treatments
                            not yet widely available:
                        </p>
                        <ul class='list-disc pl-6 space-y-2'>
                            <li>
                                <a
                                    href='#'
                                    class='text-blue-600 hover:underline'
                                    >New Zealand Clinical Trials Registry</a
                                >
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <a
                                    href='#'
                                    class='text-blue-600 hover:underline'
                                    >International Trial Participation
                                    Information</a
                                >
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <a
                                    href='#'
                                    class='text-blue-600 hover:underline'
                                    >How to Discuss Trial Participation with
                                    Your Doctor</a
                                >
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </Accordion>
            </div>
        </div>
    </main>
    <Footer />
</BaseLayout>
